  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and finely dice</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong>, then chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1688737993753-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1688737993753-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1688737993753-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1688737993753-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1688737993753-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>pork</strong> <strong>mince</strong> (remove the paper if required!) in a bowl with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>parsley</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Leave out the parsley!</span></strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up until thoroughly combined (clean hands is the best way!)</p><p>Divide equally and shape them into 3 meatballs<strong> </strong>per person</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1688737996909-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1688737996909-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1688737996909-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1688737996909-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1688737996909-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>stock</strong> <strong>mix</strong> in 125ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[185ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong></p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>cannellini</strong> <strong>beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1688738000771-x200.jpg",
