            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the meatballs are cooking, heat a pot with a drizzle of <strong>olive</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> with your <strong>dried</strong> <strong>thyme</strong> and <strong>ground smoked</strong> <strong>paprika</strong></p><p>Cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1688738007553-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1688738007553-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1688738007553-x700.jpg",
