            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1688738010842-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> in half and place in the <strong>toaster</strong> for 1-2 min or until warmed through</p><p>Spread a little <strong>butter </strong>over each <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>ciabatta</strong> <strong>half</strong></p><p>Mix the <strong>cooked meatballs</strong> through the stew – these are your <strong>Spanish-style pork meatballs with tomato & cannellini bean stew</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Keep the meatballs and stew separate!</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
